            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>When Taurus Statilius and Tiberius Platilius Aelianus were consuls. Lucius Statius Faustus before the image which he was required to set up by a law of the ministers of Fortuna Augusta, brought by the quaestor Quintus Pompeius Amethystus, they decreed that he should place two marble bases instead of a statue.</p>
